The '''1988 Tel Aviv Open''' was a [[tennis]] tournament played on [[hard court]]s that was part of the [[1988 Nabisco Grand Prix]]. It was played at the [[Israel Tennis Centers]] at [[Ramat HaSharon]] near [[Tel Aviv]] in [[Israel]] from October 10 through October 17, 1988.

==Champions==
===Men's Singles===
{{main|1988 Tel Aviv Open – Singles}}
{{flagicon|USA}} '''[[Brad Gilbert]]''' defeated {{flagicon|USA}} [[Aaron Krickstein]] 4&ndash;6, 7&ndash;6, 6&ndash;2
* It was Gilbert's only title of the year and the 14th of his career.

===Men's Doubles===
{{main|1988 Tel Aviv Open – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|BAH}} '''[[Roger Smith (tennis)|Roger Smith]]''' / {{flagicon|KEN}} '''[[Paul Wekesa]]''' defeated {{flagicon|FRG}} [[Patrick Baur]] / {{flagicon|FRG}} [[Alexander Mronz]] 6&ndash;3, 6&ndash;3
* It was Smith's only title of the year and the 1st of his career. It was Wekesa's only title of the year and the 1st of his career.

