{{refimprove|date=August 2018}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Mohammed Darweesh | image = Darwishroar-ID-4c4b3efb-06e2-44ed-a77b-0ee853cf345f.png | fullname = Mohammed Darweesh | height = {{height|m=1.86}} | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1991|6|2|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Fureidis]], [[Israel]] | currentclub = [[Hilal Al-Quds]] | clubnumber = 23 | position = [[Midfielder (association football)|Midfielder]] | youthclubs1 = [[Maccabi Haifa]] | years1 = 2010-11 | years2 = 2010-11 | years3 = 2011-12 | years4 = 2012-13 | years5 = 2013-14 | years6 = 2014-16 | years7 = 2016- | clubs1 = [[Seketzia Nes Tziona]] | clubs2 = [[F.C. Ashdod]] | clubs3 = [[Hakoah Ramat Gan]] | clubs4 = [[Hapoel Ashkelon]] | clubs5 = [[Hakoah Ramat Gan]] | clubs6 = [[Shabab Al-Dhahrieh]] | clubs7 = [[Hilal Al-Quds]] | caps1 = 5 | caps2 = 2 | caps3 = 29 | caps4 = 16 | caps5 = 19 | caps6 = 43 | caps7 = 41 | goals1 = 0 | goals2 = 0 | goals3 = 0 | goals4 = 0 | goals5 = 0 | goals6 = 4 | goals7 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2015– | nationalteam1 = [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]] | nationalcaps1 = 24 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = 9 August 2018 | nationalteam-update = 20 November 2018 }}
'''Mohammed Darweesh''' (born 2 June 1991) is a Palestinian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder (association football)|defensive Midfielder]] for [[Hilal Al-Quds]] of the [[West Bank Premier League]] and for the [[Palestine national football team]].<ref>http://www.kooora.com/?player=97184</ref>
==International Career==
Mohammed Darweesh became a key member of the [[Palestine national football team]] following the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup]]. He earned his first cap in June 2015 in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against Saudi Arabia.
Darweesh played in all six of Palestine's [[2019 AFC Asian Cup qualification]] matches helping Palestine qualify for the second ever finals tournament.
