'''Peter Charney''' (born 2 October 1989) is the current [[Guinness World Record]] holder for the most indoor [[bungee jump]]s in twenty-four hours.<ref>{{cite news|title=Going For Guinness |publisher=TIME |date=November 12, 2006 |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1558323,00.html |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110121224912/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1558323,00.html |archivedate=January 21, 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Most Bungee Jumps in 24 hours (indoors)|publisher=Guinness World Records |date=November 6, 2007|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/records-4000/most-bungee-jumps-in-24-hours-(indoors)}}</ref>

Charney first attempted the record in November 2006 as part of the Guinness World Records Day. During that attempt he completed 106 jumps in 24 hours, setting a new Guinness World Record. Due to facility issues he was forced to have a 10-hour extended break.

He completed his second successful attempt on 6&ndash;7 November 2007 in the [[West Edmonton Mall]] World Waterpark, [[Edmonton, Canada]]. After 23 hours he reached his goal of 225 jumps&mdash;averaging nine jumps per hour and up to 32 in one hour.

Both of his attempts were in support of a local charity and raised just over $5000.

