{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Swilgate | nickname = | country = England | image = Clubhouse, Tewkesbury Cricket Club - geograph.org.uk - 1036889.jpg | location = [[Tewkesbury]], [[Gloucestershire]] | establishment = 1893 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1972-1973 | club1 = [[Gloucestershire County Cricket Club|Gloucestershire]] | date = 10 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/786.html Ground profile }}
'''Swilgate''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Tewkesbury]], [[Gloucestershire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1893, when Tewkesbury played Handsworth Wood.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/786_misc.html Other matches played on Swilgate]</ref>
[[Gloucestershire County Cricket Club|Gloucestershire]] played 2 [[List-A cricket|List-A]] matches at the ground, the first of which saw them play [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire]] in the 1972 [[John Player League]]. The second and final List-A match at the ground came the following season in the same tournament when Gloucestershire played [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/786_a.html List-A Matches played on Swilgate]</ref>
[[Gloucestershire Women cricket team|Gloucestershire Women]] used the ground in the 2010 [[Women's County Championship]] Division Five South and West against [[Wiltshire Women's cricket team|Wiltshire Women]]. In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home venue of Tewkesbury Cricket Club.<ref>[http://tewkesbury.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp Tewkesbury Cricket Club]</ref>
